I popped into Urban Angel for a quick lunch bite last week and I can't decide if I'm a fan or not.
The guy who served me was really pleasant so it's nothing against the staff who are all nice and friendly, I just feel the whole place doesn't seem to fit together as well as it should.
I automatically wanted to dislike this place from the ridiculously naff name but I decided to venture in.
It took me a while to decide what I wanted from the menu, they have an excellent selection of brunch bites and I decided to go for the greek yoghurt with a seasonal fruit compote.
I'm not sure what I was expecting, perhaps some greek yoghurt with a side of fruit compote that I could mix or just eat on it's own.
I have to say, I was a little disappointed when it arrived.
It was just a bowl of yoghurt with a small amount of fruit stuck in the middle, not exactly the best way to spend £4.50.
It was okay, but nothing special, and definitely  not worth £4.50.
I sat outside and the weather was lovely and the seats were pretty comfy, I enjoyed sipping on my sparkling water and watching the world go by.
I was tempted by the delicious looking cakes but decided not to, maybe next time though.
For me, Urban Angel would be a regular haunt if the menu has a better savoury selection and the prices were a little bit cheaper or perhaps the portions a little bit bigger or better presented.
All in all, it's an okay place to grab a bite to eat.

