When I want an excellent breakfast, with the freshest ingredients cooked to the best standard, I come to Urban Angel.
It is pricey, more than I'd normally pay for a breakfast.
And in fact, it's almost so expensive that I deducted a star.
But then I thought, well, it is guaranteed excellent, fresh food every time.
It's worth it.
They do breakfast here every day, with a range of hot options and additional sides.
Eggs benny, royale etc., or poached eggs on toast, scrambled egg, an Arbroath Smokie with poached egg, and sides like portabello mushroom, spinach, grilled tomatoes, veggie haggis, regular haggis, bacon, potato scones.
There's also smoothies, juice, porridge, yoghurt, granola, and even just toast and jam.
They also have other things on the daytime menu like greek sharing boards, burgers, pasta.
It's a really unusual but nice range of breakfast, lunch and dinner.
As I said, the quality and freshness of the food is what defines it.
The food is just outstanding.
The egg yolks are bright orange.
The orange juice is freshly squeezed and has that tartness that is goooood.
I love the café too.
There's a few different rooms and the decor of wood, slate and some old-fashioned elements of the building like an old sink and wood-burning stove that show it was once maybe an old-fashioned kitchen.
I can't really put into words how or what Urban Angel is like, but if you are a visitor to the city needing breakfast, or healthy food - or if you're a local who needs a new brunch option for the weekend, or a nice bistro for an evening burger and wine - Urban Angel can do both those things, and it does it very, very well.

