Met a good friend here for a birthday brunch.
Great menu choice, attentive service & good location.
I had the beef burrito from the specials board, it came with veg rice, sour cream & guacamole.
Tasty & fresh & well seasoned with a hint of spice but not enough to make my eyes water.
It definitely hit the spot.
Mrs D had the pulled pork ciabatta which she thoroughly enjoyed.
There was at least half a pig in there & she managed to polish it off.
The homemade coleslaw earned brownie points too.
Since the sun was out & it was her birthday through the week, we both had a cheeky glass of rosé with lunch.
To finish I had the chocolate brownie & a pot of tea & Mrs D had the lemon meringue tart & a flat white.
The brownie was light but a little dry & crumbly but I still polished it off.
Mrs D said her dessert & coffee were superb.
She could give Rachel Allan a run for her money so that's high praise indeed though neither of us liked the schooshy cream on the side of the plate.
Will definitely go back.

